Buyer Beware
Aug 2015 • Solo
I visited the museum several years ago while on a tour of Vietnam. I was very impressed with the collection and its presentation. So much so that I did what I do not ordinarily do, purchase a replica in the gift shop. I was particularly interested in what was described to me as a sandstone sculpture of Shiva. It cost USD 600 at that time including shipping to the US. After a very long wait for it to arrive and process through customs I was able to place it in my garden. Within a few months and after several rainstorms I noticed the sandstone color was changing. To make a long story shorter, what was represented as sandstone turned out to be cement colored to look like sandstone. What a disappointment at such a cost! The museum totally misrepresented the item. Don't trust them.
Written July 24, 2016
