Written December 24, 2015
fieldy99
Kingscliff, Australia15 contributions
It aint the Tate but...
Jun 2015 • Friends
The Cham Museum is a good place to spend an hour or two. I have read criticisms and lack lustre reviews about the museum but really!! See the place as a public space in a low to middle income country and judge it by these standards.
The museum curates a wide range of ancient sculptures from the Champa culture. These primarily come from the My Son temple complex south west of the city (and west of Hoi An). There is a narrative around the walls about the items displayed and I learnt a good deal. When you combine the Danang facility with a visit to My Son and the visitor centre there you get a good view about this important part of the history of Vietnam. In the hotter months go early as it can get stuffy inside.
Written October 14, 2015
