Chandranath S
Pune, India222 contributions
The Musium of Cham Culture.
Mar 2015 • Friends
One feels as if one is visiting a musium of sculptures in India. The Cham musium tells us the link that existed between these countries. When you enter, your site falls on a large Shivling. There are statues of Vishnu, Ganesha, Tara, various lion shapes and typical animal shapes one sees on chariots, temples in India. The sculptures are well preserved and the placards explain you details about them. The extended section has more such sculptures and first floor gives one much more information about the trade, culture, rituals, etc. This was our first overseas visit and we choose Vietnam and Combodia to see the Heritage of our oriental cultures which spread from Hindukush mountains in Afganistan to the far away Vietnam, Combodia.
